dataIdInfo.idAbs: Space for ground and air combat forces to practice movements and tactics as specified in the unit’s Army Training and Evaluation Program (ARTEP).

prcStep.stepDesc: Schema created by SDSFIE Online: XML Workspace Generation procedure.

enttyp.enttypd: Space for ground and air combat forces to practice movements and tactics as specified in the unit’s Army Training and Evaluation Program (ARTEP).
enttyp.sdsExtDescription: Different unit types may work in support of one another (combined arms), or a unit may operate on its own to practice a specific set of ARTEP tasks.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Used to link the record to associated multimedia records that reference data.
attr.sdsExtDescription: Example media types include imagery, video, audio, scanned documents, and drawings.
attr.sdsExtNote: See your DoD Component service implementation guidance for details as to the content of this attribute.
attr.sdsExtJustification: Mandated by the IGG as a standard attribute. Intended to provide a common mechanism for linking media to entities.

attrdomv.udom: A sequence of characters from the ASCII character set.

attr.attrdef: Used to represent or link to feature level metadata.
attr.sdsExtJustification: Mandated by the IGG as a standard attribute. Intended to provide a way to link to feature level metadata records or as a way to store feature level metadata.

attrdomv.udom: A sequence of characters from the ASCII character set.

attr.attrdef: An attribute used to describe a feature required to populate the Military Installation Map (MIM) accurately.
attr.sdsExtDescription: Text, in a name or phrase, to attribute a MIM feature for adding to the MIM.
attr.sdsExtNote: Name, number, or phrase to accurately display MIM items. Example, a range number for in the Range Box.
attr.sdsExtJustification: Military Installation Maps (MIMs) are required to be produced by all Sustainable Range Program (SRP) locations. Each MIM is set up with a template that helps lay out the map and assist in creating a matching set of maps throughout SRP to represent each installation. US ARMY SRP MIM Production Specification, Appendix A, lists all the MIM data layers required in each MIM. Multiple data layers are required to contain codes to display properly on the MIM. A MIM Code attribute would is needed in order to call out these features that are required to be represented on the MIM, to include ranges, training sites, landing zones, and vegetation.

attrdomv.udom: A sequence of characters from the ASCII character set.

attr.attrdef: The designator used to identify the type of legal interest that DoD holds in a real property asset.
attr.sdsExtJustification: This attribute is necessary to ensure interoperability between IGI&S systems and Real Property systems of record and to make the IGI&S data more directly useful for the EI&E mission requirements. Required for all real property assets to which it is assigned by the IGG. CR-17-126 moved the source from the Note to the Description.

attrSdsExtEnumeration.sdsExtDefinition: The type of legal interest that the DoD holds in the Real Property Asset (RPA).
attrSdsExtEnumeration.sdsExtJustification: Added to facilitate Real Property reporting requirements.

attrSdsExtEnumerant.sdsExtDefinition: An interest that grants or restricts a right to a real property asset for a specific purpose(s).

edom.edomvd: An interest that grants or restricts a right to a real property asset for a specific purpose(s).

attrSdsExtEnumerant.sdsExtDefinition: Real property asset where a fee simple ownership interest is held by the United States government and a Military Department or WHS exercises accountability.

edom.edomvd: Real property asset where a fee simple ownership interest is held by the United States government and a Military Department or WHS exercises accountability.

attrSdsExtEnumerant.sdsExtDefinition: A mutually beneficial partnership between a Military Department or WHS and a private entity, where equity interest in a project is shared for a specific business purpose. Ownership, operations, and management rights of the real property asset are typically held by the private entity who guarantees certain use rights to the Military Department of WHS.

edom.edomvd: A mutually beneficial partnership between a Military Department or WHS and a private entity, where equity interest in a project is shared for a specific business purpose.
